      "writtenOn": "2020-04-14T21:46:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Consider\n\n    if (std::none_of(fMatrices.begin(), fMatrices.end(),\n                     [id](const auto\u0026 m) { return m.first \u003d\u003d id; }))\n\nAlso, how many marker IDs are we expecting to encounter? Is this bounded? `gather` is n^2 on the number of marker IDs, and `get` is linear when it could be constant time, but if the number of marker IDs is finite and sufficiently small, it\u0027s better to keep it simple.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 42
      },
      "revId": "a8368658eec69be45779faa918383a0cc4e0fe3e",
